INSERT INTO images VALUES('idbbbea8ed','ided86d740','Wanderer World is a vast and mysterious realm, where adventurers and nomads roam in search of new experiences and hidden treasures. The landscape is diverse, ranging from sprawling deserts to lush forests, towering mountains to serene coastlines. In this world, the journey is just as important as the destination, as wanderers traverse through ancient ruins, encounter mythical creatures, and uncover the secrets of the land. Backstory: In the beginning, "Wanderer World" was a realm lost in time and shrouded in mystery. It was believed to have been created by the convergence of ancient ley lines and the wisdom of mystical sages. The world''s diversity was a result of this convergence, as the elemental energy infused every corner of the land, giving rise to its unique and ever-changing landscapes. History: - The Age of the Elemental Convergence: A time when the elemental energies of the world were at their peak, shaping the land and giving rise to powerful artifacts and mythical creatures. - The Great Calamity: A cataclysmic event that threatened to consume "Wanderer World" in chaos and destruction. It was during this time that the legendary artifacts, such as the Crystal of Time, were created to restore balance and order. - The Rise of the Nomads: In the aftermath of the Great Calamity, nomadic wanderers emerged, drawn by the promise of adventure and the pursuit of hidden knowledge. They became the guardians of the world, ensuring that its secrets were preserved and protected. Planned Main Characters: - Elysia - Rylan - Kael - Soraya - Sorin - Starkworld Planned Special Item: - The Astral Compass Planned Significant Site: - The Citadel','491778bbce52c87632eb3c66.png',0);
INSERT INTO images VALUES('id334e4791','ida00fd73d','A fusion of tradition and modernity, Kanazawa World is a parallel universe inspired by the city of Kanazawa in Japan. It features a mix of historical landmarks, bustling cityscapes, and mystical elements. In Kanazawa World, the city is divided into two main districts: the Historical District and the Techno District. The Historical District is a charming area with beautifully preserved traditional wooden houses, Japanese gardens, and historical sites such as Kenrokuen Garden and Kanazawa Castle. The Techno District, on the other hand, is a futuristic metropolis filled with towering skyscrapers, advanced technology, and bustling streets. Both districts are connected by the mystical Kurdo River, which is believed to possess magical powers. Among the key sites in Kanazawa World are the Geisha Quarter, a vibrant district known for its geisha houses and traditional entertainment, and the Floating Sanctuary, a hidden sanctuary floating above the city where mythical creatures like dragons and phoenixes reside. Special items in Kanazawa World include the Hachibushu Artifact, an ancient relic said to grant its possessor extraordinary powers, and the Sakura Blade, a legendary sword said to be forged from petals of cherry blossoms.','13eab0cd81e1ef377fd545f8.png',0);
INSERT INTO images VALUES('id56c0250d','id364e333f','General Taldarax: A battle-hardened military leader with exceptional tactical skills, a deep sense of honor, and a commitment to protecting the galaxy from external threats. Known for his fairness and empathy, General Taldarax seeks peaceful resolutions before engaging in warfare, earning the respect of both allies and adversaries.','979440c87e30a0b86ffe8ac7.png',0);
INSERT INTO images VALUES('id72479c1f','ide5d2a50c','Harumbi is a good friend who is strong, focused, but a little slow. She is very likable and has dark hair. Harumbi is a loyal and dependable friend, always willing to lend a helping hand. Her strength and focus make her a valuable ally, and her amiable nature endears her to others, making her a trusted confidant. She often wears her dark hair in a simple and practical style, reflecting her down-to-earth personality.','84a1049824c61767d2e70242.png',0);
